Key Match Events: Federico Bikoro was sent off for a high-foot tackle on Bayo in the 55th minute
Equatorial Guinea missed a penalty in the 58th minute
Mohamed Bayo scored the winning goal in the 8th minute of stoppage time
Post-Match Reflections: Guinea ended a long sequence of losing in the AFCON knockout stages
Miscellaneous Highlights: Equatorial Guinea had finished ahead of hosts Ivory Coast and Nigeria in Group A
Others: Guinea now meet the winner of Sunday's later game between the Democratic Republic of Congo and Egypt in San Pedro
